## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-102"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.StateChanged>引發事件<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer>類別。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-102">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.StateChanged> event is raised by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-103"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.StateChangedEventArgs> 衍生自<xref:System.EventArgs>並傳遞至處理常式<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.StateChanged>事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-103"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.StateChangedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.EventArgs> and is passed to handlers for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.StateChanged> events.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-104"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.State%2A> 是唯讀的屬性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-104"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.State%2A> is a read-only property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-105">共用的語音辨識器的狀態，無法以程式設計方式變更。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-105">A shared speech recognizer's state cannot be changed programmatically.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-106">使用者可以變更使用語音辨識的使用者介面 (UI) 的共用的語音辨識器的狀態或透過**語音辨識**成員的 Windows**控制台**。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-106">Users can change a shared speech recognizer's state using the Speech Recognition user interface (UI) or through the **Speech Recognition** member of the Windows **Control Panel**.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-107">這兩個**上**並**睡眠**語音辨識的 UI 中的設定會對應到`Listening`狀態。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-107">Both the **On** and **Sleep** settings in the Speech Recognition UI correspond to the `Listening` state.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-108">**關**語音辨識的 UI 中的設定會對應到<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerState.Stopped>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-108">The **Off** setting in the Speech Recognition UI corresponds to <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerState.Stopped>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-109">下列範例會建立共用的語音辨識器，並接著會建立兩種類型的特定單字的辨識和接受免費的聽寫文法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-109">The following example creates a shared speech recognizer, and then creates two types of grammars for recognizing specific words and for accepting free dictation.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-110">此範例會以非同步方式載入所有建立的文法，辨識器。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-110">The example asynchronously loads all the created grammars to the recognizer.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-111">處理常式<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.StateChanged>事件會使用<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.EmulateRecognizeAsync%2A>把 Windows 辨識 「 接聽 」 模式的方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-111">A handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.StateChanged> event uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.EmulateRecognizeAsync%2A> method to put Windows Recognition in "listening" mode.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    private static SpeechRecognizer recognizer;  
    public static void Main(string[] args)  
    {  
  
      // Initialize a shared speech recognition engine.  
      recognizer = new SpeechRecognizer();  
  
      // Add a handler for the LoadGrammarCompleted event.  
      recognizer.LoadGrammarCompleted += new EventHandler<LoadGrammarCompletedEventArgs>(recognizer_LoadGrammarCompleted);  
  
      // Add a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
      recognizer.SpeechRecognized += new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
      // Add a handler for the StateChanged event.  
      recognizer.StateChanged += new EventHandler<StateChangedEventArgs>(recognizer_StateChanged);  
  
      // Create "yesno" grammar.  
      Choices yesChoices = new Choices(new string[] { "yes", "yup", "yah}" });  
      SemanticResultValue yesValue =  
          new SemanticResultValue(yesChoices, (bool)true);  
      Choices noChoices = new Choices(new string[] { "no", "nope", "nah" });  
      SemanticResultValue noValue = new SemanticResultValue(noChoices, (bool)false);  
      SemanticResultKey yesNoKey =  
          new SemanticResultKey("yesno", new Choices(new GrammarBuilder[] { yesValue, noValue }));  
      Grammar yesnoGrammar = new Grammar(yesNoKey);  
      yesnoGrammar.Name = "yesNo";  
  
      // Create "done" grammar.  
      Grammar doneGrammar =  
        new Grammar(new Choices(new string[] { "done", "exit", "quit", "stop" }));  
      doneGrammar.Name = "Done";  
  
      // Create dictation grammar.  
      Grammar dictation = new DictationGrammar();  
      dictation.Name = "Dictation";  
  
      // Load grammars to the recognizer.  
      recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(yesnoGrammar);  
      recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(doneGrammar);  
      recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(dictation);  
  
      // Keep the console window open.  
      Console.ReadLine();  
    }  
  
    // Put the shared speech recognizer into "listening" mode.  
    static void  recognizer_StateChanged(object sender, StateChangedEventArgs e)  
    {  
     if (e.RecognizerState != RecognizerState.Stopped)  
      {  
        recognizer.EmulateRecognizeAsync("Start listening");  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Write the grammar name and the text of the recognized phrase to the console.  
    static void  recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
     Console.WriteLine("Grammar({0}): {1}", e.Result.Grammar.Name, e.Result.Text);  
  
      // Add event handler code here.  
    }  
  
    // Handle the LoadGrammarCompleted event.  
    static void  recognizer_LoadGrammarCompleted(object sender, LoadGrammarCompletedEventArgs e)  
    {  
     string grammarName = e.Grammar.Name;  
      bool grammarLoaded = e.Grammar.Loaded;  
      if (e.Error != null)  
      {  
        Console.WriteLine("LoadGrammar for {0} failed with a {1}.",  
        grammarName, e.Error.GetType().Name);  
      }  
  
      // Add exception handling code here.  
      Console.WriteLine("Grammar {0} {1} loaded.",  
      grammarName, (grammarLoaded) ? "is" : "is not");  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="59ffa-114">下列範例會更新所提供的狀態資訊為基礎的顯示器<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerState>取自的執行個體<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.StateChangedEventArgs.RecognizerState%2A>屬性<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.StateChangedEventArgs>執行個體會傳遞至的處理常式<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.StateChanged>事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="59ffa-114">The following example updates a display based on the state information provided by a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerState> instance that is obtained from the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.StateChangedEventArgs.RecognizerState%2A> property of a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.StateChangedEventArgs> instance passed to a handler for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.StateChanged> event.</span></span>  
  
```  
  
// Make sure that _recognizer and recognition start buttons are disabled if state is stopped.  
// Re-enable the start button to allow manual re-enable if the speech recognizer is listening.  
_recognizer.StateChanged +=  
  delegate(object sender, StateChangedEventArgs eventArgs)   
{  
  _recognizerStateLabel.Text = "Speech Recognizer State: " + eventArgs.RecognizerState.ToString();  
};  
```
